`TE.chainW` (widening chain) lets each step contribute its own error variant without fighting the compiler — no manual widening needed at every link.

```ts
import { Effect, Data } from "effect";

interface Signup { readonly userId: string; readonly accepted: boolean }

class EmailInUse extends Data.TaggedError("EmailInUse")<{ readonly email: string }> {}
class WeakPassword extends Data.TaggedError("WeakPassword")<{ readonly score: number }> {}
