`Brand.nominal<Email>()` replaces the hand-rolled `_brand` cast helper — same zero-runtime cost, same nominal semantics, but the brand tag is now part of the library's machinery so refined variants compose.

`E.chainW` threads a value through functions that each return `E.Either<E_i, A>`, widening the left to `E_1 | E_2 | ...` as you go. `E.mapLeft` folds that union into one display type; `E.match` (or `E.fold`) exits the Either world into a plain value.

```ts
import { pipe } from "fp-ts/function";
import * as E from "fp-ts/Either";

type Empty = { _tag: "Empty" };
type BadLength = { _tag: "BadLength"; n: number };
type BadChars = { _tag: "BadChars" };

const nonEmpty = (s: string): E.Either<Empty, string> =>
  s.trim().length > 0 ? E.right(s.trim()) : E.left({ _tag: "Empty" });

const lenBetween = (s: string): E.Either<BadLength, string> =>
  s.length >= 3 && s.length <= 20 ? E.right(s) : E.left({ _tag: "BadLength", n: s.length });

const alnumOnly = (s: string): E.Either<BadChars, string> =>
  /^[A-Za-z0-9]+$/.test(s) ? E.right(s) : E.left({ _tag: "BadChars" });

export const validateUsername = (raw: string): string =>
  pipe(
    nonEmpty(raw),
    E.chainW(lenBetween),
    E.chainW(alnumOnly),
    E.mapLeft((e) => `invalid username (${e._tag})`),
    E.match((msg) => msg, (u) => `ok:${u}`),
  );
```

Note how the widened left `Empty | BadLength | BadChars` is exhaustively reachable in `E.mapLeft`.

```ts
import { Effect, Schedule, Console } from "effect";

interface Conn { readonly id: number }

const connect = Effect.sync((): Conn => ({ id: 1 }));
const disconnect = (c: Conn) => Console.log(`disconnect ${c.id}`);

const conn = Effect.acquireRelease(connect, (c) => disconnect(c));

let attempts = 0;
const flakyQuery = (c: Conn): Effect.Effect<string, Error> =>
  Effect.suspend(() => {
    attempts += 1;
    return attempts < 2 ? Effect.fail(new Error("flaky")) : Effect.succeed(`row@${c.id}`);
  });

const program = Effect.scoped(
  Effect.gen(function* () {
    const c = yield* conn;
    return yield* Effect.retry(flakyQuery(c), Schedule.recurs(3));
  })
);

Effect.runPromise(program).then(console.log);
```

Retries live *inside* the scoped block, so the connection is held across attempts and released once all retries succeed or exhaust.

